    "description": "Unbounded cache growth and memory leak. The _memberInfoCache uses Expression objects as dictionary keys, but Expression<T> does not implement value equality - it uses reference equality. This means two Expression objects representing the same property access will have different hash codes and won't match in the cache, creating separate entries for each unique object reference. When parent components render with inline lambdas like For="@(m => m.Property)", a new Expression object is created on each render, causing the cache to grow without bound. This results in a memory leak that accumulates with repeated component renders.",
